Exchange Terms and Conditions

Exchange is applicable only at Tanishq stores and is not applicable for an online transaction.
The stores decision on the value will be final.

General Exchange Program (Exchange of Other Jewellery Products)

i. 24kt, 22kt, 18kt Gold Jewlery products (including those not purchased from Tanishq, Zoya or Mia by Tanishq) will be accepted for exchange at Tanishq stores , as per the terms and conditions laid down by the Company.

ii. Only Plain Gold jewelry products are accepted for exchange under the policy.

iii. No exchange is available for studded products.

iv. The product/products will be valued after purity determination by the Karatmeter available at the store and melting.

v. No cash refund will be provided for exchange.

vi. Exchange is applicable only at Tanishq stores and is not applicable for an online transaction.

vii. The calculation is an approximate estimate based on online Gold rate and will vary daily based on the gold rate of that day.

viii. The Company/Titan shall not be liable for any tax implication(s) on the customer under GEP transaction.

Deductions will be applicable for exchange. For deduction details, visit your convenient store The General exchange program may be withdrawn or modified without prior notice. Any exceptions will be at the sole discretion of the company.

Tanishq Exchange Program (Exchange of Companys Jewellery Products)

Products purchased from the Website may only be exchanged at Tanishq, Mia by Tanishq or Zoya stores

1.Tanishq, Mia by Tanishq , Zoya Products Exchange :

a) Jewellery sold through any Tanishq / Mia by Tanishq / Zoya outlet or the respective brand websites, as applicable, will be accepted for exchange at the store, as per the prevailing terms and conditions of the exchange policy which is operated at the discretion of the Company

b) 24kt, 22kt, 18kt, 14kt gold and studded jewellery, and platinum jewellery will be accepted for exchange after due examination for purity, defects, weights and originality, damage or stone defects (cracks, replacements, alterations) including the Company/Brand mark / logo. In case of any discrepancy in the product, it will not be accepted for exchange.

c) For any exchange, original invoice and certificate of authenticity must be produced.

d) The terms for valuation of the product is given below,

i. Gold / plain platinum products will be valued at 100% prevailing metal rate at the respective stores on the day of exchange.

ii. Diamonds (on studded gold / platinum products) will be valued at 100% prevailing stone rate on the day of exchange.

iii. Solitaire (loose solitaire/ Studded gold or platinum solitaire jewellery) will be valued at 100% prevailing stone rate if customer buys studded gold / studded platinum product against the exchange

iv. Solitaire (loose solitaire/ Studded gold or platinum solitaire jewellery) will be valued at 90% prevailing stone rate if the customer buys plain gold / plain platinum product or coin against exchange.

v. No exchange for Solitaires of 2 carats and above

vi. Other Studded products will be valued at 80% of prevailing value of the product

vii. Any other category of products not mentioned above will need to be checked with the respective stores for the prevailing terms and conditions

viii. Making charges, taxes, and any discount given on the original invoice, will be deducted in full.

ix. The Company/Titan shall not be liable for any tax implication(s) on the customer under TEP transaction.

The exchange program may be withdrawn or modified without prior notice. Any exceptions will be at the sole discretion of the company

For more details on the exchange, you can contact our nearby store or contact our customer care

Buying Guide

The Diamond Guide

The Gemstone Guide

The Metal Guide

While the shape of a diamond is not a part of the four Cs, it is indirectly attributed to the cut. The shape of diamond plays an important role in the selection of any diamond, as it determines the style and appeal of the jewellery piece it is set in. Diamonds from Tanishq are available in a wide range of shapes, including: round, princess, emerald, square, oval, radiant, pear, heart, marquise and cushion shaped.

Cut The cut of a diamond is defined by its proportions, its symmetry and its polish. The expertise with which these steps of the cutting process have been executed determine the performance of the cut diamond. A polished diamonds beauty is shaped by its complex relationship with light. The amazing display you see when looking at a diamond is a combination of three attributes:

Brightness is the combined effect of all white light reflecting from the interior and the surface of a diamond.

Fire or dispersion, describes the flashes of rainbow colour emitted from a diamond.

Scintillation describes the interplay of light and dark areas and the sparkle you see when the diamond, the light, or the onlooker moves.

Diamonds from Tanishq are available in a wide range of shapes, including: round, princess, emerald, square, oval, radiant, pear, heart, marquise and cushion shaped.

Cut The cut of a diamond is defined by its proportions, its symmetry and its polish. The expertise with which these steps of the cutting process have been executed determine the performance of the cut diamond. A polished diamonds beauty is shaped by its complex relationship with light. The amazing display you see when looking at a diamond is a combination of three attributes:

Brightness is the combined effect of all white light reflecting from the interior and the surface of a diamond.

Fire or dispersion, describes the flashes of rainbow colour emitted from a diamond.

Scintillation describes the interplay of light and dark areas and the sparkle you see when the diamond, the light, or the onlooker moves.

While the shape of a diamond is not a part of the four Cs, it is indirectly attributed to the cut. The shape of diamond plays an important role in the selection of any diamond, as it determines the style and appeal of the jewellery piece it is set in.
